HEADWORD: Hebetation
<hw>Heb`e*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>hebetatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>h⟦eacute⟧b⟦eacute⟧tation</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of making blunt, dull, or stupid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being blunted or dulled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hebete</ent>⟦br⟧
